note._content: SS Birkenhead, built by J Pashley of Balmain in 1888 for the Balmain Steam Ferry Company. Taken over by the Balmain New Ferry Company in 1906. Sank at Dawes Point on 15th May 1913 after her steering jammed and she crashed into a pontoon.
